Will you allow Rotom to enter the motor?

There is a mysterious notebook here. Its age is
{pageend:impossible to tell.}
“It was by pure chance that I obtained
{pageend:information about the Pokémon Rotom.}
“Remarkably, Rotom is able to merge with
{pageend:special motors.}
“Rotom can thereby enter various home
{pageend:appliances and change its form.}
“I have confirmed that Rotom changes its types
and the moves it can learn by reflecting the
{pageend:characteristics of any home appliance it enters.}
“This Pokémon requires exhaustive observation
{pageend:and analysis.}
“To ensure I get all the credit, my Rotom
{pageend:research must be kept secret.}
“They will come to recognize me as the
{pageend:scientific genius Char...”}
The rest of the notebook is blank.

{pageend:Ah, imagine finding you here!}
You must be eager to fill your Pokédex to be
{pageend:searching even here.}
{pageend:What am I doing?}
{pageend:I visit a professor I know in Eterna every so often.}
He tells me intriguing rumors of rare Pokémon
sightings and such.

A Pokémon that slips into electric appliances,
{pageend:you say...}
Hmm... That is somewhat off from what I’ve
{pageend:heard about it.}
{pageend:Hmm... This is what I’ve heard.}
Long ago, there was a Pokémon that merged with
{pageend:a toy robot.}
Should that Pokémon be recognized as a new
{pageend:species or not?}
Debates over the issue were about to start when
{pageend:they were rendered moot.}
The very topic of discussion—the Pokémon-
infused robot—disappeared...

It’s an old notebook. There’s no telling how old
{pageend:it is.}
Would you like to read it?

{pageend:“Our encounter was a sudden one.}
“It was when I found my toy robot—one that I
{pageend:had earlier misplaced.}
“At that instant, a Pokémon startlingly emerged
{pageend:from the lawn mower’s motor!}
“Clutching my robot, I stared, transfixed by the
{pageend:peculiar Pokémon.”}
Would you like to keep reading?

“The Pokémon hovered in the air, held aloft by a
{pageend:power unseen.}
“As if curious and unafraid of my presence, it
{pageend:floated toward me.}
“Crackling sounds accompanied it, as if from
{pageend:static electricity in the air.}
“Remarkably, it seemed the Pokémon was the
{pageend:source of this power!}
“In alarm, I flinched, certain that my face would
{pageend:be subjected to a shock.}
“Much to my surprise, the Pokémon seemed to
{pageend:favor me with a smile.”}
Would you like to keep reading?

“Finally, I came to realize that the Pokémon only
{pageend:wished to be friends.}
“I have decided to name this most wondrous
{pageend:Pokémon ‘Rotom.’}
“Simple though it may be, Rotom emerged to me
{pageend:from the motor of a lawn mower.}
“‘Motor’ and ‘Rotom’... Surely the link
{pageend:is obvious?”}
Would you like to keep reading?

{pageend:“Rotom is a Pokémon that is simply sensational.}
“The fact that it can turn invisible is simply
{pageend:the beginning.}
“What makes Rotom unique is its ability to enter
{pageend:and operate machinery!”}
This is about halfway through. Would you like to
keep reading?

“Rotom and I became fast friends. We were
{pageend:perpetual companions.}
“The electricity from its body forbade
{pageend:contact, however.}
“We could not touch, let alone hug or hold
{pageend:hands, but we cared not.}
“For we were bonded on a much deeper,
{pageend:incorporeal level.”}
Would you like to keep reading?

“A feeling of mischief got the better of me
{pageend:one day.}
“Seeing Rotom hovering, I decided to startle it.
{pageend:Normally I would not.}
“Perhaps frightened, Rotom discharged power
{pageend:beyond its usual range.}
“I fell, stunned, into the arms
{pageend:of unconsciousness...”}
Would you like to keep reading?

“When I came to, to my horror I realized that
{pageend:Rotom had disappeared.}
“I searched high and low for my friend in dismay
{pageend:and desperation.}
{pageend:“‘Don’t chastise yourself.’}
{pageend:“‘The fault is mine. No harm done.’}
{pageend:“‘Let us play as we always have.’}
“Though my words poured out, my friend could
{pageend:not be found to hear them...”}
Would you like to keep reading?

{pageend:“My search for Rotom carried me far from home.}
“It was in the town’s rubbish heap that I again
{pageend:found my old toy robot.}
“Curiously, our eyes met, then the robot waved a
{pageend:hand as if in greeting.}
{pageend:“I knew then that I had found my lost friend.}
“I ran to it and hugged Rotom tight, talking on
{pageend:and on.”}
Would you like to keep reading?

{pageend:“The robot’s eyes lit up happily as I held it.}
“I’m certain that within it, Rotom was emitting
{pageend:lots of electricity.}
“Somehow, I felt I could understand Rotom’s
{pageend:thoughts better than before.}
“Also, I realized that we would remain friends
{pageend:throughout our lives...”}
The notebook ends with this page.

