{tag:2} emerged from the motor.

Anyway, this Rotom...
{pageend:What an interesting Pokémon.}
So, you say it enters an appliance and essentially
{pageend:merges with the device.}
{pageend:It may also learn new moves in the process.}
In a way, I suppose it could be thought of as a
{pageend:mechanical Pokémon.}
Hmm! Though it is utterly unique, it is undeniably
{pageend:a species of Pokémon.}
{pageend:Fine, fine, so be it!}
No matter how old one gets, there will always be
{pageend:new Pokémon discoveries!}
Take care, {tag:0}!

{pageend:What’s this?!}
You went to the Distortion World and
{pageend:battled with the legendary GIRATINA?!}
Remarkable. Truly remarkable!
{pageend:This is absolutely unprecedented!}
At any rate, you are indeed worthy of
meeting Legendary Pokémon, {tag:0}{pageend:!}
I’m positive they would appear before
{pageend:you if you go to the right place.}
Please ask me about anything that
you would like to know.

Incidentally, and this is an entirely
{pageend:different topic...}
I’ve heard that there have been
{pageend:sightings of very rare Pokémon.}
The legendary bird Pokémon: ARTICUNO,
{pageend:ZAPDOS, and MOLTRES!}
They’ve been spotted at various
{pageend:locations here in Sinnoh, no less!}
Why, you may be lucky enough to see
them yourself in your journeys!

ARTICUNO, ZAPDOS, and MOLTRES
{pageend:are extremely rare even in Kanto.}
There have been precious few sightings
{pageend:as it is.}
So why would they be spotted here in
{pageend:Sinnoh of all places?}
There are still many, many mysteries
surrounding Pokémon, it seems!

Take a look at the two feathers
I have here, {tag:0}{pageend:.}
They’re both known as Clear Wings.
{pageend:You might think they look ordinary...}
But these feathers have a puzzle that
{pageend:I’m currently trying to solve.}
They may have a connection to the two
Pokémon known as the guardians of the
{pageend:sea and sky.}
Lugia, the guardian of the sea, is
said to mediate between the three
{pageend:legendary birds of Kanto.}
Maybe this Clear Wing would react to
{pageend:Articuno, Zapdos and Moltres?}
If you were to go somewhere very cold,
somewhere that generates electricity,
{pageend:and somewhere where Trainers gather...}
Well, it would be an amazing encounter
to see any of them, that’s for sure!

Now, this other Clear Wing...
{pageend:Perhaps it could be the Rainbow Wing?}
The guardian of the sky was said to
{pageend:have resurrected three Pokémon.}
Raikou, Entei and Suicune.
{pageend:The legendary beasts of Johto.}
I’m sure this Clear Wing would respond
{pageend:to the presence of those Pokémon!}
I would imagine those Pokémon would
{pageend:enjoy high places...}
Maybe the Rock Climb technique could
{pageend:help you find them?}
If you somehow catch all three...
Please show them to me.

What’s this? In your party...
{pageend:Articuno, Zapdos and Moltres?!}
Now that is incredible!
Thank you, {tag:0}{pageend:.}
Now, this Clear Wing...
Will it react, I wonder?

Ah, splendid! It really did work!
{pageend:This Clear Wing has changed.}
It’s now a deep silver colour...
{pageend:And it’s sparkling, too.}
{pageend:It must be the Silver Wing!}
Thanks for your assistance, {tag:0}.
I’d like you to have this Silver Wing.

In your party...
{pageend:Raikou, Entei, and Suicune?!}
You’ve done it again, {tag:0}!
{pageend:Truly impressive!}
{pageend:Now, let’s see if this Clear Wing...}
Oh?!

Oh, yes, there was something
{pageend:I had to tell you.}
The three Pokémon of the lakes appear
{pageend:to have returned to their homes.}
Oh, yes. I’ve also heard reports that
{pageend:strange Pokémon have appeared in Sinnoh.}
It’s likely that their appearance is a
result of the events that occurred
{pageend:with Dialga and Palkia at Mt. Coronet.}
Hm! Perhaps that Red Chain you have
{pageend:could be the key to that mystery?}
So, tell me.
{pageend:How are things going for you?}
{pageend:The Pokédex...?}
Hm! A total of {tag:0}!
{pageend:...And the number of Badges?}
Well! You’ve got seven already!
{pageend:That only leaves Sunyshore’s Gym.}
Hm! You’ve come this far.
{pageend:Why not obtain Sunyshore’s Badge?}
And why not challenge the Pokémon
{pageend:League?}
That will broaden your horizons
{pageend:further than ever before.}
Not to mention the opportunities to
meet even more Pokémon.

Oh, yes, {tag:0}{pageend:.}
If you see Cynthia, please give her 
my best regards.

Do you know the names of any
other Pokémon professors, {tag:0}{pageend:?}
I can assure you there are many more
{pageend:than just myself and Professor Rowan!}
{pageend:Elm, Birch, Juniper, Sycamore, Kukui...}
All of these names belong to fellow
Pokémon professors around the world!

I should inform you that my full
{pageend:name is Professor Samuel Oak.}
I have a cousin in Alola who is known
{pageend:as Professor Samson Oak!}
His research focuses on the regional
{pageend:variants found in Alola.}
Did you know that the Vulpix in Alola
are Ice-type, rather than Fire-type?

{pageend:I have a grandson called Blue.}
He was the Champion of the Kanto
{pageend:Pokémon League, in fact.}
Though only for a brief time.
{pageend:Then he lost to his rival, Red.}
At least Blue found a place as the
{pageend:Viridian City Gym Leader!}
Though he’s often away from it,
{pageend:causing trouble for challengers.}
That boy...

Oh, yes. I once had a protégé who
{pageend:very much enjoyed outdoor research.}
His name is Professor Willow.
{pageend:He used to study Pokémon under me.}
Him and his assistants are always
making strides in Pokémon research!

Have you ever thought of yourself
as a photographer, {tag:0}{pageend:?}
I once invited a talented young man
to take photos of Pokémon in their
{pageend:natural habitat.}
It was a place called Pokémon Island...
{pageend:And what a beautiful place it was!}
The young photographer helped me
with completing my Pokémon Report!
